ior and prefer it for *all* \"global\" modules I need to install... I\u0027m glad to see others on board.\n\nI will happily make the `~/.node` method on the same level as `npm install -g`"},{"file":"README.md","line":22,"reviewer":{"name":"Kody A Kantor","email":"kody.kantor@joyent.com","username":"KodyKantor"},"message":"Maybe we can mention whatever the NPM issue is that we usually refer to when folks have this issue. That would make this sentence sound more confident."},{"file":"README.md","line":22,"reviewer":{"name":"Dave Eddy","email":"dave.eddy@joyent.com","username":"bahamas10"},"message":"Agreed, I\u0027ll refactor this readme to make the ~/.node method a more viable option"},{"file":"README.md","line":55,"reviewer":{"name":"Kody A Kantor","email":"kody.kantor@joyent.com","username":"KodyKantor"},"message":"I\u0027m not a huge fan of the word \u0027otherwise\u0027 here, but I can\u0027t think of better wording. I think it would be nice if we could refer to the home-directory-global-style install in some way.\n\nIf we used the bulleted layout in the \u0027installation\u0027 section we could use the same scheme here and it would match nicely."},{"file":"README.md","line":55,"reviewer":{"name":"Dave Eddy","email":"dave.eddy@joyent.com","username":"bahamas10"},"message":"agreed.  will make changes in a new patchset"}],"files":[{"file":"/COMMIT_MSG","type":"ADDED","insertions":7,"deletions":0},{"file":"README.md","type":"MODIFIED","insertions":89,"deletions":-39}],"sizeInsertions":89,"sizeDeletions":-39},{"number":"2","revision":"83b94146ae081d845a10a3836690439aad940ef5","parents":["f8d9342e8fe1d27ebdf304b283d2f4ec77b77e02"],"ref":"refs/changes/19/4719/2","uploader":{"name":"Dave Eddy","email":"dave.eddy@joyent.com","username":"bahamas10"},"createdOn":1534799931,"author":{"name":"Dave Eddy","email":"dave.eddy@joyent.com","username":"bahamas10"},"isDraft":false,"kind":"TRIVIAL_REBASE","approvals":[{"type":"CI-Testing","description":"CI-Testing","value":"1","grant